{
  "id": "ALSA-2022:6437",
  "summary": "Moderate: kernel-rt security and bug fix update",
  "details": "The kernel-rt packages provide the Real Time Linux Kernel, which enables fine-tuning for systems with extremely high determinism requirements.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* Incomplete cleanup of multi-core shared buffers (aka SBDR) (CVE-2022-21123)\n* Incomplete cleanup of microarchitectural fill buffers (aka SBDS) (CVE-2022-21125)\n* Incomplete cleanup in specific special register write operations (aka DRPW) (CVE-2022-21166)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nBug Fix(es):\n\n* The latest AlmaLinux 8.6.z3 kernel changes need to be merged into the RT source tree to keep source parity between the two kernels. (BZ#2111112)",
